# Import data
def read_sensor_data(folder_path):
  all_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(folder_path, "sensor_data_*.csv"))
  dfs = []

  # loop over sensor data files in folder
  for f in all_files:
    df = pd.read_csv(f, names=["timestamp", "acc_x", "acc_y", "acc_z", "gyr_x", "gyr_y", "gyr_z"])

    # transform timestamp column
    df["timestamp"] = round((df["timestamp"] - df["timestamp"].iloc[0]) / pow(10, 9), 2)

    df = df.sort_values("timestamp")

    df = df.drop_duplicates("timestamp")

    df['timestamp'] = pd.to_timedelta(df['timestamp'], unit='S')

    # # Set the timestamp column as the index
    # df.set_index('timestamp', inplace=True)

    # Resample the data to regular 100ms intervals
    df_resampled = df.resample('100ms', on="timestamp").mean()

    # Interpolate missing values in the acc_x column
    df_resampled = df_resampled.interpolate()

    # Reset the index to numeric sequential values
    df_resampled.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

    df_resampled.insert(0, "timestamp", df_resampled.index*0.1)

    df_resampled = df_resampled[df_resampled["timestamp"] <= 1000]

    # extract activity from filename and insert activity column
    activity = os.path.splitext(os.path.basename(f))[0].split("_")[2]
    df_resampled.insert(0, "activity", activity)

    dfs.append(df_resampled)

  merged_df = pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)
  return merged_df

# Assign dataframe
df = read_sensor_data("C:\\Users\\hammi\\Data Projects\\sensor_data")

def map_activity(df):

  activities = df["activity"].unique()

  activity_mapping = {activity: index for index, activity in enumerate(activities)}

  df["activity"] = df["activity"].map(activity_mapping)

  print(activity_mapping)

  return df

df = map_activity(df)

{'driving': 0, 'sitting': 1, 'stationary': 2, 'walking': 3}

# Train test split

def train_test_split(df):
    train_data = []
    test_data = []

    for activity in df["activity"].unique():
        train_size = int(0.8 * max(df[df["activity"]==activity]["timestamp"]))
        train_data.append(df[df["timestamp"] < train_size])
        test_data.append(df[df["timestamp"] >= train_size])

    train_data = pd.concat(train_data, ignore_index=True)
    test_data = pd.concat(test_data, ignore_index=True)

    return train_data, test_data

train_data, test_data = train_test_split(df)

def compute_dominant_frequency(window):
  fft_values = np.fft.fft(window)  # Apply FFT
  power_spectrum = np.abs(fft_values) ** 2  # Calculate power spectrum
  frequencies = np.fft.fftfreq(len(window))
  peaks, _ = find_peaks(power_spectrum, height=0)  # Find peaks in the power spectrum

  dominant_frequency_index = peaks[np.argmax(power_spectrum[peaks])]  # Index of the peak with highest power
  dominant_frequency = frequencies[dominant_frequency_index]  # Dominant frequency value

  return dominant_frequency

# Windows
def create_windows(train_data, test_data):
  window_size = 20
  step_size = 20

  for column in df.columns:
    if column not in ["timestamp", "activity"]:
      rolling_mean_column = f"rolling_{column}_mean"
      rolling_std_column = f"rolling_{column}_std"
      dominant_frequency_column = f"dominant_{column}_frequency"

      train_data[rolling_mean_column] = train_data.groupby("activity")[column].rolling(window=window_size).mean().reset_index(level=0, drop=True)
      train_data[rolling_std_column] = train_data.groupby("activity")[column].rolling(window=window_size).std().reset_index(level=0, drop=True)
      # train_data[dominant_frequency_column] = train_data.groupby("activity")[column].rolling(window=window_size).apply(compute_dominant_frequency).reset_index(level=0, drop=True)

      test_data[rolling_mean_column] = test_data.groupby("activity")[column].rolling(window=window_size).mean().reset_index(level=0, drop=True)
      test_data[rolling_std_column] = test_data.groupby("activity")[column].rolling(window=window_size).std().reset_index(level=0, drop=True)
      # test_data[dominant_frequency_column] = test_data.groupby("activity")[column].rolling(window=window_size).apply(compute_dominant_frequency).reset_index(level=0, drop=True)

  train_data = train_data.iloc[::step_size].dropna().reset_index(drop=True)
  test_data = test_data.iloc[::step_size].dropna().reset_index(drop=True)

  train_data = train_data.drop(["timestamp", "acc", "gyr"], axis=1)
  test_data = test_data.drop(["timestamp", "acc", "gyr"], axis=1)

  return train_data, test_data

train_data, test_data = create_windows(train_data, test_data)

def create_x_y_train_test(train_data, test_data):
  target = "activity"
  features = list(train_data.columns.drop([target]))
  X_train = train_data[features]
  X_test = test_data[features]
  y_train = train_data[target]
  y_test = test_data[target]

  scaler = StandardScaler()
  X_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
  X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)

  return X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test

X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test = create_x_y_train_test(train_data, test_data)
